This metrical or rhythmic accent is not to be confounded with the grammatical accent, with which, however, it often coincides. The law of accentuation in Latin is simply that “the main accent falls on the antepenultimate syllable (i.e. last syllable but two), except when the penultimate (i.e. last syllable but one) is long 3 in which case it falls on that.'' There is no accent on the last syllable. Thus Interea, intima& intrcire.
